<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880106-0042 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Technodyne Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TND </CO><IN> BBK ERN </IN><TEXT>   Technodyne Inc., a wholesale distributor of pharmaceuticals, said it acquired about 2.9 million of its common shares from Electro Audio Dynamics Inc. principally in exchange for assuming $4.3 million of its bank debt.    Electro Audio's sole holding was an 81.5% stake in Technodyne. As a result of the agreement, it now holds about 1.1 million, or about 55%, of Technodyne's two million shares outstanding, Technodyne said. The holding company's debt had been in technical default, it said.    Both companies are based in Great Neck, N.Y.    Technodyne also reported net income of $1 million, or 21 cents a share, based on the old number of shares outstanding, for its year ended Aug. 1, 1987. Based on the new number of shares outstanding, per-share net was 51 cents. For fiscal 1986, the company had a net loss of $6.7 million. </TEXT></DOC>